Ben Ames Williams ( 7 March 1889 â€“ 4 February 1953 ) American writer who published over thirty novels , including The Strange Woman ( 1945 ) , House Divided ( 1947 ) , Leave Her to Heaven ( 1946 ) , and Come Spring ( 1940 ) . His writing traversed a wide range of genres and evinced considerable expertise in a number of divergent fields . Williams achieved his greatest popularity when two of his books , Leave Her to Heaven , The Strange Woman , and All the Brothers Were Valiant were adapted to film . Lives of Mississippi Authors , 1817 - 1967 . Jackson : University Press of Mississippi , 467 - 469 . This American novelist article is a stub . You can help by expanding it . 